Text.SourceString: Good day, stranger!//Oh, you just moved to the farm? Welcome to the community.//<portrait=normal>My name is <NPCName>Anne</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Good day, stranger!//Oh, you just moved to the farm? Welcome to the community.//<portrait=normal>My name is <NPCName>Anne</>.

Text.SourceString: A quick word of advice from your new neighbor.//Be patient! Since last year, those darn crops aren’t growing like they used to.
Text.LocalizedString: A quick word of advice from your new neighbor.//Be patient! Since last year, those darn crops aren’t growing like they used to.

Text.SourceString: They’re talking about building a community garden someday. You must have heard, right?//We offered the space behind our house, but I don’t think anybody much likes the idea.
Text.LocalizedString: They’re talking about building a community garden someday. You must have heard, right?//We offered the space behind our house, but I don’t think anybody much likes the idea.

Text.SourceString: It’s too far from the town and whatnot. Oh well!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s too far from the town and whatnot. Oh well!

Text.SourceString: I need to drop off my recycling before going shopping tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to drop off my recycling before going shopping tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: I wonder where we’ll put our recycling once the bin is full…
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder where we’ll put our recycling once the bin is full…

Text.SourceString: Not everybody has one of those fancy compact recycling machines.//<portrait=concerned>Ah, you know – the little machine that you put in your yard? Don’t you have one?//<portrait=happy>Oh well. No point complaining about it.
Text.LocalizedString: Not everybody has one of those fancy compact recycling machines.//<portrait=concerned>Ah, you know – the little machine that you put in your yard? Don’t you have one?//<portrait=happy>Oh well. No point complaining about it.

Text.SourceString: If you grow soybeans, you can use them to make tempeh. Neat, eh?
Text.LocalizedString: If you grow soybeans, you can use them to make tempeh. Neat, eh?

Text.SourceString: You do need a press to make tempeh, though.
Text.LocalizedString: You do need a press to make tempeh, though.

Text.SourceString: I’m trying to find time to edit all this video footage before the deadline.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m trying to find time to edit all this video footage before the deadline.

Text.SourceString: You can’t always spot wild animals. Sometimes they stay in hiding because they’re too shy to come out.//Wild animals might have already made a home at your farm, but you wouldn’t even know.//Happens to us a lot. That’s why we leave fodder for them in an open shed. It’s free food!
Text.LocalizedString: You can’t always spot wild animals. Sometimes they stay in hiding because they’re too shy to come out.//Wild animals might have already made a home at your farm, but you wouldn’t even know.//Happens to us a lot. That’s why we leave fodder for them in an open shed. It’s free food!

Text.SourceString: There could be luwaks at your farm, or maybe bees. If you build a bee house, it might encourage them to come out.//Make them feel comfortable, that’s the trick.
Text.LocalizedString: There could be luwaks at your farm, or maybe bees. If you build a bee house, it might encourage them to come out.//Make them feel comfortable, that’s the trick.

Text.SourceString: Having a busy Thursday, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Having a busy Thursday, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Yeah, us too.//<portrait=happy>Oh, you know, the usual. Wildlife…blah, blah, blah.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, us too.//<portrait=happy>Oh, you know, the usual. Wildlife…blah, blah, blah.

Text.SourceString: Having a busy Friday, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Having a busy Friday, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Yeah, us too.//<portrait=happy>Oh, you know, the usual. Wildlife…blah, blah, blah.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, us too.//<portrait=happy>Oh, you know, the usual. Wildlife…blah, blah, blah.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know how safe it is to live in the forest, especially with small children.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know how safe it is to live in the forest, especially with small children.

Text.SourceString: The woodland is as close as I’ll let <NpcName>Zoe</> get.
Text.LocalizedString: The woodland is as close as I’ll let <NpcName>Zoe</> get.

Text.SourceString: I think I’ll make some gnocchi and hummus for dinner.//Make a little extra for tomorrow too.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I’ll make some gnocchi and hummus for dinner.//Make a little extra for tomorrow too.

Text.SourceString: Oh no. I don’t think I have any tomatoes.//<portrait=concerned>Oh well! Hummus it is.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh no. I don’t think I have any tomatoes.//<portrait=concerned>Oh well! Hummus it is.

Text.SourceString: It’s great that <NpcName>Paul</> and I can observe wildlife around the clock, since we’re surrounded by nature.//But I also like that the woodland is so close to the school.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s great that <NpcName>Paul</> and I can observe wildlife around the clock, since we’re surrounded by nature.//But I also like that the woodland is so close to the school.

Text.SourceString: As a mom, I worry all the time. I don’t like <NpcName>Zoe</> walking too far, especially on rainy days.
Text.LocalizedString: As a mom, I worry all the time. I don’t like <NpcName>Zoe</> walking too far, especially on rainy days.

Text.SourceString: If you look closely in the trees, you may notice some birds’ nests.//<portrait=normal><NpcName>Zoe</> gets really excited when she spots one.
Text.LocalizedString: If you look closely in the trees, you may notice some birds’ nests.//<portrait=normal><NpcName>Zoe</> gets really excited when she spots one.

Text.SourceString: Oh, so you’ve done all your farming chores for the day?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, so you’ve done all your farming chores for the day?

Text.SourceString: Let me get this straight. You quit your job and moved to Coral Island to become a farmer?
Text.LocalizedString: Let me get this straight. You quit your job and moved to Coral Island to become a farmer?

Text.SourceString: That sounds so exciting!//<NpcName>Paul</> and I should make a documentary about you one day. It would be different from what we usually do, but it sure would be inspiring.
Text.LocalizedString: That sounds so exciting!//<NpcName>Paul</> and I should make a documentary about you one day. It would be different from what we usually do, but it sure would be inspiring.

Text.SourceString: We want to get those little video cameras that attach to your hat. That way, we could capture more footage.
Text.LocalizedString: We want to get those little video cameras that attach to your hat. That way, we could capture more footage.

Text.SourceString: But it’s a little outside our budget right now. Oh well! It’s not the end of the world.
Text.LocalizedString: But it’s a little outside our budget right now. Oh well! It’s not the end of the world.

Text.SourceString: It takes us days and sometimes weeks to capture the best wildlife footage.
Text.LocalizedString: It takes us days and sometimes weeks to capture the best wildlife footage.

Text.SourceString: In this job, I believe patience is key.
Text.LocalizedString: In this job, I believe patience is key.

Text.SourceString: Your farm is pretty close to the ocean. I don’t know if that’s a good or a bad thing for spotting nocturnal animals.
Text.LocalizedString: Your farm is pretty close to the ocean. I don’t know if that’s a good or a bad thing for spotting nocturnal animals.

Text.SourceString: Hmm… It would be interesting to observe wildlife behavior in different settings.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm… It would be interesting to observe wildlife behavior in different settings.

Text.SourceString: There will be plenty of time for <NpcName>Zoe</> to go on adventures. For now, I think it’s safer for her to focus on school.
Text.LocalizedString: There will be plenty of time for <NpcName>Zoe</> to go on adventures. For now, I think it’s safer for her to focus on school.

Text.SourceString: I can’t do my shopping on the weekend.//I’d have to take <NpcName>Zoe</> with me, and she’d want to buy all the cookies.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t do my shopping on the weekend.//I’d have to take <NpcName>Zoe</> with me, and she’d want to buy all the cookies.

Text.SourceString: She can be quite strong willed. It’s easier for me to just shop during the week.
Text.LocalizedString: She can be quite strong willed. It’s easier for me to just shop during the week.

Text.SourceString: It’s <NpcName>Paul’s</> birthday this weekend. To be honest, I haven’t gotten anything for him yet.//I hope there’s still time.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s <NpcName>Paul’s</> birthday this weekend. To be honest, I haven’t gotten anything for him yet.//I hope there’s still time.

Text.SourceString: There’s still time to make jam, I suppose!//That’ll be perfect. He loves jam.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s still time to make jam, I suppose!//That’ll be perfect. He loves jam.

Text.SourceString: I think I saw a couple of beavers swimming in the lake on my way here.//Did you see them too?
Text.LocalizedString: I think I saw a couple of beavers swimming in the lake on my way here.//Did you see them too?

Text.SourceString: Ah, that reminds me! I need to ask <NpcName>Paul</> to bring in some extra blankets from the shed now that it’s getting colder.//I’ll just ask him tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, that reminds me! I need to ask <NpcName>Paul</> to bring in some extra blankets from the shed now that it’s getting colder.//I’ll just ask him tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: Phew! Good thing we found extra blankets right before all these. I really need to organize stuff better.
Text.LocalizedString: Phew! Good thing we found extra blankets right before all these. I really need to organize stuff better.

Text.SourceString: What a pain to dig them up. I need boxes so I can label them. It would make things easier to find next year.
Text.LocalizedString: What a pain to dig them up. I need boxes so I can label them. It would make things easier to find next year.

Text.SourceString: Some animals only come out when it rains. Have you noticed that too?
Text.LocalizedString: Some animals only come out when it rains. Have you noticed that too?

Text.SourceString: I always need to be ready in case we have to run out and film.
Text.LocalizedString: I always need to be ready in case we have to run out and film.

Text.SourceString: Watch your boots, will ya?
Text.LocalizedString: Watch your boots, will ya?

Text.SourceString: I might open up the windows tonight so we can hear the rain.
Text.LocalizedString: I might open up the windows tonight so we can hear the rain.

Text.SourceString: Let’s just hope there isn’t a storm.
Text.LocalizedString: Let’s just hope there isn’t a storm.

Text.SourceString: It’s so humid today. Even the rain hasn’t helped to break this humidity.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s so humid today. Even the rain hasn’t helped to break this humidity.

Text.SourceString: It’s Summer after all. What else can you expect?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s Summer after all. What else can you expect?

Text.SourceString: It’s so humid today.//Oh gosh!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s so humid today.//Oh gosh!

Text.SourceString: A little rain wouldn’t hurt, I don’t think.
Text.LocalizedString: A little rain wouldn’t hurt, I don’t think.

Text.SourceString: Some animals only come out when it rains. Have you noticed that too?
Text.LocalizedString: Some animals only come out when it rains. Have you noticed that too?

Text.SourceString: I always need to be ready in case we have to run out and film.
Text.LocalizedString: I always need to be ready in case we have to run out and film.

Text.SourceString: Keep your jacket on, <PlayerName>$player</>! It’s freezing out.
Text.LocalizedString: Keep your jacket on, <PlayerName>$player</>! It’s freezing out.

Text.SourceString: Watch your boots, will ya?
Text.LocalizedString: Watch your boots, will ya?

Text.SourceString: If we were living in the middle of the forest, what would we do during a snowstorm like this?
Text.LocalizedString: If we were living in the middle of the forest, what would we do during a snowstorm like this?

Text.SourceString: All right, it may not be a storm, but it’s so cold out it might as well be. Some animals are in their hideouts. They need to keep warm, you know.//<portrait=normal>Just like us.
Text.LocalizedString: All right, it may not be a storm, but it’s so cold out it might as well be. Some animals are in their hideouts. They need to keep warm, you know.//<portrait=normal>Just like us.

Text.SourceString: If we were living in the middle of the forest, what would we do during a snowstorm like this?
Text.LocalizedString: If we were living in the middle of the forest, what would we do during a snowstorm like this?

Text.SourceString: All right, it may not be a storm, but it’s so cold out it might as well be. Some animals are in their hideouts. They need to keep warm, you know.//<portrait=normal>Just like us.
Text.LocalizedString: All right, it may not be a storm, but it’s so cold out it might as well be. Some animals are in their hideouts. They need to keep warm, you know.//<portrait=normal>Just like us.

Text.SourceString: I wonder how long the snow will last. I’m not complaining though.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder how long the snow will last. I’m not complaining though.

Text.SourceString: I’m here to pick up some groceries for the week. Hopefully, I’ll get everything I need.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m here to pick up some groceries for the week. Hopefully, I’ll get everything I need.

Text.SourceString: I always seem to forget something. I wonder if that’s a grocery thing.
Text.LocalizedString: I always seem to forget something. I wonder if that’s a grocery thing.

Text.SourceString: As soon as I get home, I’ll realize I forgot to buy something.//<portrait=concerned>It’s pretty annoying, if you ask me.
Text.LocalizedString: As soon as I get home, I’ll realize I forgot to buy something.//<portrait=concerned>It’s pretty annoying, if you ask me.

Text.SourceString: Write it down? Ha! That’s an idea.//<portrait=happy>All right. Maybe…
Text.LocalizedString: Write it down? Ha! That’s an idea.//<portrait=happy>All right. Maybe…

Text.SourceString: I can’t ask <NpcName>Paul</> to get groceries. He’d just forage some vegetables by the lake or something and bring them home.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t ask <NpcName>Paul</> to get groceries. He’d just forage some vegetables by the lake or something and bring them home.

Text.SourceString: I mean, there’s nothing wrong with wild vegetables.//<portrait=annoyed>But they’re different.
Text.LocalizedString: I mean, there’s nothing wrong with wild vegetables.//<portrait=annoyed>But they’re different.

Text.SourceString: If you need a carrot, you can’t just come home with kale…//Or a fig.//You can’t substitute just anything for anything.
Text.LocalizedString: If you need a carrot, you can’t just come home with kale…//Or a fig.//You can’t substitute just anything for anything.

Text.SourceString: So you woke up holding an egg and somehow didn’t break it in your sleep?
Text.LocalizedString: So you woke up holding an egg and somehow didn’t break it in your sleep?

Text.SourceString: Okay. That’s a funny story, but I still don’t know why you’re telling me all this.
Text.LocalizedString: Okay. That’s a funny story, but I still don’t know why you’re telling me all this.

Text.SourceString: *mumbling* Milk, eggs…
Text.LocalizedString: *mumbling* Milk, eggs…

Text.SourceString: I wonder if I should get a couple bottles of milk instead of just one. But I don’t want it to go bad if nobody drinks it.//That would be such a waste.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder if I should get a couple bottles of milk instead of just one. But I don’t want it to go bad if nobody drinks it.//That would be such a waste.

Text.SourceString: See, I knew it!//I forgot to pick up some oil. We’re running out, and I don’t know what I’ll do.//<portrait=normal>Hey! What’s up?
Text.LocalizedString: See, I knew it!//I forgot to pick up some oil. We’re running out, and I don’t know what I’ll do.//<portrait=normal>Hey! What’s up?

Text.SourceString: Oh, don’t worry about the mess. It’s never neat in here!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, don’t worry about the mess. It’s never neat in here!

Text.SourceString: Just try not to step on anything, will you?
Text.LocalizedString: Just try not to step on anything, will you?

Text.SourceString: We don’t have any tea, but would you like some warm hummus, maybe?
Text.LocalizedString: We don’t have any tea, but would you like some warm hummus, maybe?

Text.SourceString: When you encounter wildlife, make sure to keep your distance. If you get too close, you’ll scare them.
Text.LocalizedString: When you encounter wildlife, make sure to keep your distance. If you get too close, you’ll scare them.

Text.SourceString: It’s important to keep a safe distance from wild animals so they don’t attack.//I really don’t want to lecture you. But the number of people who don’t know any better is shocking.//<portrait=annoyed>And not in a good way, you know. Shockingly bad!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s important to keep a safe distance from wild animals so they don’t attack.//I really don’t want to lecture you. But the number of people who don’t know any better is shocking.//<portrait=annoyed>And not in a good way, you know. Shockingly bad!

Text.SourceString: Soybean cakes are best sliced thinly and fried.
Text.LocalizedString: Soybean cakes are best sliced thinly and fried.

Text.SourceString: They’re really easy to overeat. I can down plates of them in one go.
Text.LocalizedString: They’re really easy to overeat. I can down plates of them in one go.

Text.SourceString: We usually have a beach day on the weekend and just play some volleyball or something.//I’m looking forward to it.
Text.LocalizedString: We usually have a beach day on the weekend and just play some volleyball or something.//I’m looking forward to it.

Text.SourceString: I don’t think I could manage if our house was any bigger.//We’d just keep piling things in it.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t think I could manage if our house was any bigger.//We’d just keep piling things in it.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Paul</> is no good at keeping the house clean.//I mean, you’ve seen him. Well, that goes for both of us, actually. We both spend our time outdoors, in literal mud sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Paul</> is no good at keeping the house clean.//I mean, you’ve seen him. Well, that goes for both of us, actually. We both spend our time outdoors, in literal mud sometimes.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Zoe</> keeps me busy all day with her mischief.//I can barely keep up with her. You’ll see, she’ll come home with <NPCName>Goddess</> knows what tomorrow!
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Zoe</> keeps me busy all day with her mischief.//I can barely keep up with her. You’ll see, she’ll come home with <NPCName>Goddess</> knows what tomorrow!

Text.SourceString: That was too harsh. She’s a sweetheart, she <Italic>is</>, but it’s not easy keeping her in line.//Especially when it comes to homework.
Text.LocalizedString: That was too harsh. She’s a sweetheart, she <Italic>is</>, but it’s not easy keeping her in line.//Especially when it comes to homework.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Zoe</> needs to focus on school right now. I don’t mean she can’t go on adventures. Homework comes first and adventuring second. She’ll have plenty of time for adventures in the future.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Zoe</> needs to focus on school right now. I don’t mean she can’t go on adventures. Homework comes first and adventuring second. She’ll have plenty of time for adventures in the future.

Text.SourceString: I hate to nag, but nothing else seems to be working.
Text.LocalizedString: I hate to nag, but nothing else seems to be working.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Dippa</>? Yeah, I see them around the island, painting.//They’re very quiet, so they don’t scare the wildlife very much.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Dippa</>? Yeah, I see them around the island, painting.//They’re very quiet, so they don’t scare the wildlife very much.

Text.SourceString: They live next to us. Sometimes we share fertilizer or the harvest from our gardens, but that’s about it.//<portrait=normal><NpcName>Dippa</> and <NpcName>Emma</> keep to themselves most of the time.
Text.LocalizedString: They live next to us. Sometimes we share fertilizer or the harvest from our gardens, but that’s about it.//<portrait=normal><NpcName>Dippa</> and <NpcName>Emma</> keep to themselves most of the time.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Zoe</> <Italic>what</>?
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Zoe</> <Italic>what</>?

Text.SourceString: I told her so many times to never go past the recycling center.//Yet for some reason, I keep hearing this from <NpcName>Emma</>. And now you.
Text.LocalizedString: I told her so many times to never go past the recycling center.//Yet for some reason, I keep hearing this from <NpcName>Emma</>. And now you.

Text.SourceString: Documentaries are tricky, especially when they’re about wildlife.//We really can’t predict when we’ll be able complete a project.
Text.LocalizedString: Documentaries are tricky, especially when they’re about wildlife.//We really can’t predict when we’ll be able complete a project.

Text.SourceString: All right, that’s fair. Our problem now isn’t getting the footage, it’s editing. I just mean there are ups and downs in this job.//<portrait=happy>I wouldn’t trade it for anything, though. We always have fun.
Text.LocalizedString: All right, that’s fair. Our problem now isn’t getting the footage, it’s editing. I just mean there are ups and downs in this job.//<portrait=happy>I wouldn’t trade it for anything, though. We always have fun.

Text.SourceString: I hate it when I forget something at the store.//<portrait=concerned>It’s like my brain decides to play tricks on me, and I end up remembering everything but the one thing I needed.
Text.LocalizedString: I hate it when I forget something at the store.//<portrait=concerned>It’s like my brain decides to play tricks on me, and I end up remembering everything but the one thing I needed.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Paul’s</> a good guy, but sometimes I think he lives in a different world.//I mean, who goes fishing for vegetables?//<portrait=normal>He’s silly that way. I guess that’s what made me fall for him.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Paul’s</> a good guy, but sometimes I think he lives in a different world.//I mean, who goes fishing for vegetables?//<portrait=normal>He’s silly that way. I guess that’s what made me fall for him.

Text.SourceString: It’s funny how one missing ingredient can ruin a whole recipe.//<portrait=concerned>You can’t substitute just anything for anything. Trust me, I’ve tried.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s funny how one missing ingredient can ruin a whole recipe.//<portrait=concerned>You can’t substitute just anything for anything. Trust me, I’ve tried.

Text.SourceString: Summer’s a mixed bag, you know? I love the long days and warm nights, but the humidity can be brutal. It’s a trade-off.//<portrait=concerned>It’s like the air is clinging to your skin.
Text.LocalizedString: Summer’s a mixed bag, you know? I love the long days and warm nights, but the humidity can be brutal. It’s a trade-off.//<portrait=concerned>It’s like the air is clinging to your skin.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Zoe</> loves the outdoors, but I always make sure to keep her safe.//The woodland has the perfect balance of adventure and security.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Zoe</> loves the outdoors, but I always make sure to keep her safe.//The woodland has the perfect balance of adventure and security.

Text.SourceString: I always get a little nervous when there’s a storm coming.
Text.LocalizedString: I always get a little nervous when there’s a storm coming.

Text.SourceString: Our show, Friends with Wildlife, has been a labor of love.//We want to show people how amazing and important these animals are and why we need to protect them.
Text.LocalizedString: Our show, Friends with Wildlife, has been a labor of love.//We want to show people how amazing and important these animals are and why we need to protect them.

Text.SourceString: I heard from <NpcName>Paul</> that you watched Friends with Wildlife back in Pokyo?//<portrait=happy>That’s amazing. Thank you for your support.
Text.LocalizedString: I heard from <NpcName>Paul</> that you watched Friends with Wildlife back in Pokyo?//<portrait=happy>That’s amazing. Thank you for your support.

Text.SourceString: I can’t help but worry about <NpcName>Mark</> all the time. He’s always dealing with who knows what.//At least with him living here in Starlet Town, I can <Italic>babysit</> him.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t help but worry about <NpcName>Mark</> all the time. He’s always dealing with who knows what.//At least with him living here in Starlet Town, I can <Italic>babysit</> him.

Text.SourceString: Mom’s always sending me letters, asking if my brother’s okay.//<portrait=annoyed>She’s so worried about him, and I am too.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom’s always sending me letters, asking if my brother’s okay.//<portrait=annoyed>She’s so worried about him, and I am too.

Text.SourceString: I keep telling <NpcName>Mark</> he needs to write back to Mom.//He writes, yes, just not often.//<portrait=annoyed>He needs to send her things too so she knows he still loves her.
Text.LocalizedString: I keep telling <NpcName>Mark</> he needs to write back to Mom.//He writes, yes, just not often.//<portrait=annoyed>He needs to send her things too so she knows he still loves her.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes I feel like I’m the only one who cares about <NpcName>Mark’s</> safety.//He takes so many risks, and he doesn’t always think things through.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes I feel like I’m the only one who cares about <NpcName>Mark’s</> safety.//He takes so many risks, and he doesn’t always think things through.

Text.SourceString: I don’t think <NpcName>Mark</> cares about <NpcName>Mark’s</> safety!
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t think <NpcName>Mark</> cares about <NpcName>Mark’s</> safety!

Text.SourceString: I’m proud of <NpcName>Mark</>, I am. Even though I worry about him <Italic>constantly</>.//<portrait=normal>I’m proud of everything he’s accomplished.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m proud of <NpcName>Mark</>, I am. Even though I worry about him <Italic>constantly</>.//<portrait=normal>I’m proud of everything he’s accomplished.

Text.SourceString: He’s such an adventurer, always exploring and taking risks. He’s inspiring, really.//<portrait=happy>In a way, we’re both dedicating our lives to wildlife.
Text.LocalizedString: He’s such an adventurer, always exploring and taking risks. He’s inspiring, really.//<portrait=happy>In a way, we’re both dedicating our lives to wildlife.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Mark</> is like a magnet for animals. Dogs, especially.//<portrait=normal>He’s great with them. He and Bonbon are like two peas in a pod.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Mark</> is like a magnet for animals. Dogs, especially.//<portrait=normal>He’s great with them. He and Bonbon are like two peas in a pod.

Text.SourceString: My brother’s teaching <NpcName>Zoe</> how to defend herself.//<portrait=annoyed>With her interest in exploring the woods, gosh, we need it.
Text.LocalizedString: My brother’s teaching <NpcName>Zoe</> how to defend herself.//<portrait=annoyed>With her interest in exploring the woods, gosh, we need it.

Text.SourceString: The other day, I saw them gardening together.//<NpcName>Zoe</> loves her Uncle <NpcName>Mark</>.
Text.LocalizedString: The other day, I saw them gardening together.//<NpcName>Zoe</> loves her Uncle <NpcName>Mark</>.

Text.SourceString: You’ve done great things for the community, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//<portrait=happy>You’re a caring person, I can tell.
Text.LocalizedString: You’ve done great things for the community, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//<portrait=happy>You’re a caring person, I can tell.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Paul</> talks about borrowing <NpcName>Theo’s</> boat. It does sound fun, but I’m not sure if the boat could fit all of us.//<portrait=annoyed>Besides, it’s pretty <Italic>old</>.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Paul</> talks about borrowing <NpcName>Theo’s</> boat. It does sound fun, but I’m not sure if the boat could fit all of us.//<portrait=annoyed>Besides, it’s pretty <Italic>old</>.

Text.SourceString: Good thing it isn’t going to rain today.//I’ve been looking forward to the beach all week.
Text.LocalizedString: Good thing it isn’t going to rain today.//I’ve been looking forward to the beach all week.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Paul</> and <NpcName>Zoe</> teamed up to play pranks on me last week.//<portrait=annoyed>They put a cutout picture of a face inside a jar in the fridge. My heart jumped for sure. I might’ve jumped too. I don’t remember.//They think they’re so funny!
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Paul</> and <NpcName>Zoe</> teamed up to play pranks on me last week.//<portrait=annoyed>They put a cutout picture of a face inside a jar in the fridge. My heart jumped for sure. I might’ve jumped too. I don’t remember.//They think they’re so funny!

Text.SourceString: I love their pranks.//It shows how close they are.
Text.LocalizedString: I love their pranks.//It shows how close they are.

Text.SourceString: There’s something magical about the snow.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s something magical about the snow.

Text.SourceString: Even though it can get pretty cold, I still love Winter.//<portrait=happy>Plus, seeing NpcName>Archie</> building a snowman the other day made me so happy. It took me back to when I was a kid.
Text.LocalizedString: Even though it can get pretty cold, I still love Winter.//<portrait=happy>Plus, seeing NpcName>Archie</> building a snowman the other day made me so happy. It took me back to when I was a kid.

Text.SourceString: The Winter Fair is always so festive and joyful. I love seeing all the lights and decorations.
Text.LocalizedString: The Winter Fair is always so festive and joyful. I love seeing all the lights and decorations.

Text.SourceString: The Winter Fair is always so festive and joyful. I love seeing all the lights and decorations.//I’m <Italic>so</> looking forward to it.

Text.SourceString: I’ve bundled <NpcName>Zoe</> up for Winter.//Wool socks, wool beanie.
